  "body": "When I Ctrl+C trinity, I always see a timeout waiting for the networking process to clean itself up, at which point it returns anyway, leaving running tasks behind and causing those asyncio ERRORS\r\n\r\n```\r\n    INFO  06-15 09:16:00     service  Timed out waiting for <trinity.nodes.ropsten.RopstenLightNode object at 0x7f3b67fd3d68> to finish its cleanup, exiting anyway\r\n   ERROR  06-15 09:16:00  base_events  Task was destroyed but it is pending!\r\ntask: <Task pending coro=<Event.wait() running at /usr/lib/python3.6/asyncio/locks.py:283> wait_for=<Future cancelled>>\r\n    INFO  06-15 09:16:00         ipc  Sent SIGTERM to process 17368, waiting 3 seconds for it to terminate\r\n    INFO  06-15 09:16:00        main  Networking process (pid=17368) terminated\r\n```",
